a-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qzp1665702925713.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qzp1665702925713.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qzp1665702925713.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qzp1665702925713\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Tuning Tips for Microsoft SQL Server\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Microsoft SQL Server can be tuned to improve performance with a Uniface application.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d356393e56\">\n                     \n SQL Profiler\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qzp1665702925713__p_d46856e1_d46857e1_d46858e1\">You can monitor the performance of DBMS events corresponding to Uniface operations using SQL Profiler. SQL Profiler is a Microsoft SQL server tool that can help to detect the database problem and also help to optimize the SQL server database.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qzp1665702925713__p_d46859e1_d46860e1_d46861e1\">Use the following setting in the assignment file of the Uniface Application Server:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nmss=U3.0 \nUSYS$MSS_PARAMS mapping:2,procs:on,ri:dbms</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qzp1665702925713__p_d46862e1_d46863e1_d46864e1\">For every database I/O operation (<code class=\"ph codeph\">retrieve</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">store</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">update</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">delete</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">insert</code>) performed on the Uniface client application, note the corresponding stored procedures or SQL statement executed on the SQL server. The performance problems are associated with the time it takes to execute <code class=\"ph codeph\">insert</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">update</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">select</code> statements.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qzp1665702925713__p_d46865e1_d46866e1_d46867e1\">To analyze performance:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qzp1665702925713__li_d23393e1_d23394e1_d23395e1\">Start the SQL Profiler and start a trace—Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt;New &gt;Trace…</span></span> on the SQL Server.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qzp1665702925713__li_d23396e1_d23397e1_d23398e1\">To capture the triggers or stored procedures, set the <code class=\"ph codeph\">SP:StmtCompleted</code> options—Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Trace Properties &gt;Events tab &gt;Stored Procedures</span></span> to choose the events you want to monitor.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qzp1665702925713__li_d23399e1_d23400e1_d23401e1\">View the trace data. The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">TextData</span> trace data column identifies the trigger or stored procedure names from the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">TextData</span> column. This also displays the code found within the trigger or stored procedure itself. You can copy and paste the trigger code into Query Analyzer for further troubleshooting and query analysis.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531489\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531489\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Tuning Tips for Microsoft SQL Server Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Tuning Tips for Microsoft SQL Server The Microsoft SQL Server can be tuned to improve performance with a Uniface application. SQL Profiler You can monitor the performance of DBMS events corresponding to Uniface operations using SQL Profiler. SQL Profiler is a Microsoft SQL server tool that can help to detect the database problem and also help to optimize the SQL server database. Use the following setting in the assignment file of the Uniface Application Server: [DRIVER_SETTINGS] mss=U3.0 USYS$MSS_PARAMS mapping:2,procs:on,ri:dbms Copy For every database I/O operation ( retrieve , store , update , delete , and insert ) performed on the Uniface client application, note the corresponding stored procedures or SQL statement executed on the SQL server. The performance problems are associated with the time it takes to execute insert , update and select statements. To analyze performance: Start the SQL Profiler and start a trace—Choose File >New >Trace… on the SQL Server. To capture the triggers or stored procedures, set the SP:StmtCompleted options—Choose Trace Properties >Events tab >Stored Procedures to choose the events you want to monitor. View the trace data. The TextData trace data column identifies the trigger or stored procedure names from the TextData column. This also displays the code found within the trigger or stored procedure itself. You can copy and paste the trigger code into Query Analyzer for further troubleshooting and query analysis. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}